abstract: The gunman was identified by Russian news outlets as a 39-year-old loner who owned seven rifles.
snippet: The gunman was identified by Russian news outlets as a 39-year-old loner who owned seven rifles.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — The gunman who attacked the headquarters of Russia’s feared security agency this week and killed one of its agents was an unemployed security guard and gun enthusiast, various Russian news outlets reported on Friday.

abstract: The investigation against President Clinton was thorough and nonpartisan. The Trump proceedings have been the opposite in every way.
snippet: The investigation against President Clinton was thorough and nonpartisan. The Trump proceedings have been the opposite in every way.
lead_paragraph: As I walked into the House chamber on Wednesday evening, I had flashbacks to a sadly familiar scene. Just a day short of 21 years ago, I had cast my votes to impeach President Bill Clinton and was then selected to serve as a House manager — a prosecutor — to argue our case before the Senate. While the Clinton impeachment was a bitterly divisive moment in our history, I did what I believed — and still believe — was right.

abstract: Nothing to hide, nothing to fear? Think again.
snippet: Nothing to hide, nothing to fear? Think again.
lead_paragraph: The surveillance state is the stuff of dystopian novels and futuristic thrillers. Or, as revealed in the Video Op-Ed above, it’s here now. With ad trackers on our phones, facial recognition cameras on our streets and N.S.A. agents listening in on our phone calls, Big Brother is watching.

abstract: Wisconsin Gov. Tony Evers said Friday he will not consider a pardon request from a man convicted of rape and murder when he was a teenager whose story was documented in the 2015 Netflix series “Making a Murderer.”
snippet: Wisconsin Gov. Tony Evers said Friday he will not consider a pardon request from a man convicted of rape and murder when he was a teenager whose story was documented in the 2015 Netflix series “Making a Murderer.”
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — Wisconsin Gov. Tony Evers said Friday he will not consider a pardon request from a man convicted of rape and murder when he was a teenager whose story was documented in the 2015 Netflix series “Making a Murderer.”
headline_main: Wisconsin Governor Rejects 'Making a Murderer' Pardon Bid
headline_print_headline: Wisconsin Governor Rejects 'Making a Murderer' Pardon Bid

abstract: A young hitchhiker’s encounter with the famous author’s macabre imagination.
snippet: A young hitchhiker’s encounter with the famous author’s macabre imagination.
lead_paragraph: It was a Sunday night in 1971. The sky was black. The road was black. I couldn’t see my feet. I couldn’t see where the tarmac ended and the grass verge began. I had to get home to Aylesbury that night. I was 19.

abstract: British prosecutors said on Friday they had decided to charge the wife of a U.S. diplomat over a fatal car crash in England and to seek her extradition, a decision that "disappointed" Washington.
snippet: British prosecutors said on Friday they had decided to charge the wife of a U.S. diplomat over a fatal car crash in England and to seek her extradition, a decision that "disappointed" Washington.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — British prosecutors said on Friday they had decided to charge the wife of a U.S. diplomat over a fatal car crash in England and to seek her extradition, a decision that "disappointed" Washington.
headline_main: UK Prosecutors to Charge U.S. Diplomat's Wife Over Fatal Car Crash
headline_print_headline: UK Prosecutors to Charge U.S. Diplomat's Wife Over Fatal Car Crash

abstract: A policy which allows British security service agents to commit serious criminal activities including violence is lawful, a tribunal ruled by a slim majority on Friday.
snippet: A policy which allows British security service agents to commit serious criminal activities including violence is lawful, a tribunal ruled by a slim majority on Friday.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — A policy which allows British security service agents to commit serious criminal activities including violence is lawful, a tribunal ruled by a slim majority on Friday.
headline_main: UK Policy to Allow Secret Agents to Commit Crimes Is Lawful, Tribunal Rules
headline_print_headline: UK Policy to Allow Secret Agents to Commit Crimes Is Lawful, Tribunal Rules

abstract: Catalan separatist leaders Carles Puigdemont and Antoni Comin received temporary accreditation as members of the European Parliament on Friday, a day after the European Union's highest court issued a ruling with favorable implications for them.
snippet: Catalan separatist leaders Carles Puigdemont and Antoni Comin received temporary accreditation as members of the European Parliament on Friday, a day after the European Union's highest court issued a ruling with favorable implications for them.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — Catalan separatist leaders Carles Puigdemont and Antoni Comin received temporary accreditation as members of the European Parliament on Friday, a day after the European Union's highest court issued a ruling with favorable implications for them.
headline_main: After Court Ruling, Catalan Separatists Get Temporary Badges as EU Lawmakers
headline_print_headline: After Court Ruling, Catalan Separatists Get Temporary Badges as EU Lawmakers
